div.div: Commented on #31366 Add ability to manage dock size via command/shortcut
Sounds like another vouch for having zero parameters in the bulk actions? Yep, no params for open actions, and only one param for active actions.
Commented on #31366 Add ability to manage dock size via command/shortcut

remove any parameters from the workspace::DecreaseOpenDocksSize and make them use the default from the other command I think we can remove the "open"s' parameters and make them inherit from the "active"s'. keep a single parameter in the Increase/DecreaseActiveDockSize Due to it accepting f32, is it possible to use negative values already? If it is, it can be merged into a single, ChangeActiveDockSize action. If someone wants to increase it, they must also want to decrease it. There are already many actions like this, such as Increase/DecreaseBufferFontSize . I think we shouldnâ€™t break this. Hackers who want some of their panels to grow differently will be able to bind another keybinding manually. After some thought, I believe we can use a single percentage parameter. Docks grow up based on the percentage of the remaining space, which could create a pretty balanced view. Unlike the current implementation, the first dock in the all_docks() will always be adjusted first. For example, if I hold the workspace::DecreaseOpenDocksSize shortcut, the left dock will fill in the entire background finally. Using a percentage parameter allows us to achieve a balanced view, and the width and height are adjusted dynamically, solving the issues we previously worried about.
